{
  "schemaVersion": "1.16.0",
  "board": {
    "metadata": {
      "id": "_w6jix_-YGsyXYv-8ICmD",
      "name": "Maker Chip PCB - V4",
      "author": "Kevin Fehr",
      "description": "40 mm diameter poker-chip-form-factor device built as **three separate single-/double-sided PCBs** that are soldered together into a 3.6 mm stack (0.8 mm top + 2.0 mm middle + 0.8 mm bottom). Three LISOCLU HUAN159 cool-white (6500K) double-ended flexible LED filaments, cut from 300mm stock to 24mm (18mm active LED area with 12 dies + 3mm stripped silicone per end for soldering), are mounted into 20mm recessed slots in the top PCB with ~1mm clearance per side. Driven independently by an ATtiny85 (SOIC-8) on PB0 / PB1 / PB4 PWM through 56 Ω 0603 series resistors at ~36mA per channel. Powered through an 8-pad pogo-pin interface on the bottom face — VCC and GND pads sit at the magnet centers for even pogo contact force. Layer bonding via either aligned through-stack vias soldered at each section, or castellated half-plated edges soldered around the perimeter — TBD. LED filaments sourced from Amazon (ASIN B0DGPY5WLZ).",
      "createdAt": 1773807557620,
      "updatedAt": 1779856639401,
      "version": 28
    },
