            "design_rules": [
              "Never exceed 5.5 V on VCC; absolute max 6.0 V.",
              "Per-pin DC current must not exceed 40 mA (recommend < 20 mA continuous).",
              "Total DC current into VCC or out of GND must not exceed 200 mA.",
              "External I2C pull-ups mandatory on PB0/SDA and PB2/SCL.",
              "Reserve PB5/RESET unless specifically using as I/O.",
              "OC0B and OC1A share PB1 — only one PWM per physical pin.",
              "Decouple VCC with 0.1 uF as close to pin 8 as possible.",
              "RC oscillator has ±10% accuracy uncalibrated; use crystal or OSCCAL for timing-critical apps.",
              "SOIC-8 narrow body footprint requires a reflow-compatible land pattern (1.27 mm lead pitch, ~5.4 x 6.0 mm courtyard)."
            ],
            "warnings": [
              "Driving >40 mA into any I/O pin will damage the part.",
              "Driving >200 mA cumulative through VCC/GND will damage the part.",
              "Static discharge can latch up CMOS inputs.",
              "Clearing RSTDISBL fuse is HVSP-only reversible.",
              "Operating beyond speed-vs-voltage curve yields unreliable execution.",
              "USI is not a hardware UART — software UART libraries required.",
              "SOIC-8 is NOT breadboard-friendly. For breadboard use the PDIP variant or a SOIC-to-DIP adapter."
            ],
            "application_examples": [
              "Three-channel LED driver (filament, candle simulator, color-changing badge) on reflow-assembled PCB",
              "Capacitive-touch input controller",
              "Standalone PWM dimmer",
              "Bit-banged I2C/SPI sensor bridge",
              "Production version of a hobbyist PDIP prototype"
            ],
            "compatibility_notes": "Same die as PDIP ATTINY85-20PU. Programmable via AVR ISP (MISO=PB1, MOSI=PB0, SCK=PB2, RESET=PB5). Supported by ATTinyCore + PlatformIO. SPI/I2C via USI — TinyWireM/TinyWireS/USIWire libraries. SOIC-8 narrow body land pattern: KiCad 'Package_SO:SOIC-8_3.9x4.9mm_P1.27mm', Eagle 'SOIC-8' (1.27 mm), Altium 'SOIC127P490X175-8N'.",
            "usage_notes": "Use SOIC-8 when moving from breadboard prototype to reflow-assembled PCB. Same pinout, fuses, peripherals, and Arduino-IDE workflow as PDIP — only footprint and assembly change.",
            "node_geometry": {
              "xScale": 1,
              "yScale": 1,
              "outline": {
                "preset": "rounded_rectangle"
              }
            }
          },
