          "id": "c6382f2d-9ca7-4f58-bd4a-748fc4e43895",
          "title": "Decide interlayer bonding: aligned vias vs castellated edges",
          "description": "Pick (a) aligned through-stack vias at each section (cheap PCB, more PCB real estate consumed by via fields, requires precise drill alignment across 3 separately fab'd layers) or (b) castellated / half-plated edges (cleaner aesthetic, easier perimeter reflow/hand-solder, slightly higher fab cost from edge plating on all 3 layers, no internal real estate cost). Decision must be finalized before middle-layer cutout pattern and before Gerbers are generated.",
          "status": "todo",
          "createdAt": 1778795341084,
