          "title": "Place 8 pogo pads on bottom PCB (VCC/GND on magnet centers)",
          "description": "Lay out 8× 3 mm circular ENIG-finish pads on the bottom face of the bottom PCB. Pad 1 (VCC) and Pad 2 (GND) sit concentric with the two magnet positions (one magnet each), so pogo-pin contact pressure is reacted directly through the magnetic mate. Signal pads 3-8 are distributed around the 40 mm perimeter at a uniform pitch — exact pitch TBD by Gerber-time. No solder mask over pads (must remain exposed copper). Avoid placing pads in the bonding ring needed for vias / castellation.",
          "status": "todo",
          "createdAt": 1778796646806,
          "updatedAt": 1778796646806
        },
        {
          "id": "a02dc52b-a91e-4ef0-92e7-f02563073281",
          "title": "Resolve ATtiny85 SOIC-8 vs library PDIP-8 mismatch — RESOLVED",
          "description": "Resolved by creating a sibling ProtoPart branch `new/attiny85-soic8` (commit ea70485) that clones the PDIP electrical block verbatim and swaps only the mechanical/package/purchaseInfo fields. The library will host BOTH variants (`attiny85` for PDIP, `attiny85-soic8` for SOIC). The Protoboard board template was updated to the SOIC-8 mechanical profile (4.9 × 3.9 × 1.75 mm, SOIC-8 8S2, smt_reflow). Electrical interface IDs are identical between variants, so all 10 ATtiny instance bindings stayed valid through the swap. Post-swap DRC: 14/17 still green, only the 3 accepted ATtiny↔Filament architectural reds remain.",
