      "tags": [
        "LED",
        "PCB",
        "pogo-pin",
        "wearable"
      ],
      "notes": "## Form Factor\n- **Diameter**: 40 mm (poker chip)\n- **Total stacked thickness**: 3.6 mm (0.8 + 2.0 + 0.8 mm)\n- **Construction**: three separate single/double-sided PCBs soldered together post-fab — NOT a single multi-layer board\n- **Layer bonding (TBD)**: either (a) aligned through-stack vias soldered at each section to tie the three layers, or (b) castellated / half-plated edges so the perimeter can be reflowed / hand-soldered around the rim. Affects via real-estate on top/bottom and edge-plating cost on all three.\n\n## Stack Structure\n- **Top PCB (0.8 mm)**: Silkscreen design on top face. Bottom face holds the 3 filament solder pads, the 3× 56 Ω 0603 resistors, and the ATtiny85 SOIC-8. **Each filament solder pad pair sits over a 20mm cutout slot in the top PCB so the filament body drops into the slot and sits flush** — stripped ends soldered to pads, active LED area recessed in slot.\n- **Middle PCB (2 mm)**: Cutouts for the filament slots (aligned with top), resistors, the ATtiny85 (SOIC-8 is ~1.75 mm tall — fits easily), and 2 magnet pockets. Two 15 mm × 2 mm magnets with opposing polarities drop into the middle slot and are sandwiched by the top + bottom PCBs.\n- **Bottom PCB (0.8 mm)**: 8× 3 mm circular copper pads on the bottom face for pogo-pin contact. Traces and optional components on the top face. **VCC (Pad 1) and GND (Pad 2) are centered on the two magnet positions so the pogo force is balanced through the magnetic mate.** Remaining 6 signal pads distributed around the chip.\n\n## LED Filament — LISOCLU HUAN159 (Changed from Adafruit ADA-6141)\n- **Purchased part**: LISOCLU 300mm Double-Ended Flexible LED Filament, 6500K Cool White\n- **Amazon ASIN**: B0DGPY5WLZ\n- **Purchase URL**: https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DGPY5WLZ\n- **Color**: 6500K Cool White (changed from 2700K Warm White)\n- **Connection type**: Double-ended — anode (V+) on one end, cathode (GND) on opposite end (changed from single-ended)\n- **Stock length**: 300mm with ~200 LED dies at ~1.5mm pitch\n- **Cut to**: 24mm total (18mm active LED area with 12 dies + 3mm stripped silicone per end)\n- **PCB slot**: 20mm rectangle — 18mm active LEDs sit centered with ~1mm clearance per side\n- **Vf**: ~3V (same as before — LEDs in parallel, voltage independent of length)\n- **Max current (25mm cut)**: 50mA (per Adafruit ADA6139 reference for identical 25mm length)\n- **Actual drive current**: ~36mA at 56Ω from 5V supply\n- **CRI**: 85\n- **Diameter**: ~2mm (silicone-coated FPC)\n- **PWM dimmable**: Yes\n- **Manufacturer datasheet**: None available (generic Shenzhen COB component). Cross-reference: Adafruit ADA-6139 (25mm cool white, same spec class) and CY-FRX3002-M2001 factory datasheet (300mm variant).\n- **Cutting notes**: Cut between LED dies (visible through translucent silicone). Strip ~3mm silicone from each end to expose FPC substrate pad for soldering. LEDs wired in parallel — remaining segment works after cutting.\n\n## Why the LED change (V4 revision)\n- Switched from Adafruit ADA-6141 (warm white, single-ended, 25mm) to LISOCLU HUAN159 (cool white, double-ended, cut from 300mm)\n- **Reason**: Double-ended connection preferred — anode and cathode on opposite ends for cleaner routing through the 20mm PCB slot. Cool white (6500K) chosen for aesthetic preference.\n- **Source**: Amazon (ASIN B0DGPY5WLZ) preferred over direct Chinese sellers for return policy protection on unbranded parts.\n- **Resistor unchanged**: 56Ω YAGEO RC0603FR-0756RL remains correct — 36mA drive current is within both the LED's 50mA limit and ATtiny85's 40mA/pin absolute max.\n\n## Component Footprints\n| Part | Package | Height |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| ATtiny85 MCU | SOIC-8 (ATTINY85-20SU) | ~1.75 mm |\n| 56 Ω resistor | 0603 SMD | ~0.45 mm |\n| LISOCLU filament | 24mm cut (18mm active in 20mm slot + 3mm stripped ends) | ~2mm diameter |\n| Pogo pads | 3 mm diameter circular Cu | ENIG-plated, 35 µm |\n\n## 8-Pad Standard Interface (bottom face)\n| Pad | Signal | ATtiny85 Pin | Direction | Position note |\n|-----|--------|--------------|-----------|---------------|\n| 1 | VCC (5 V) | Pin 8 | external → MCU | centered on magnet A |\n| 2 | GND | Pin 4 | reference | centered on magnet B |\n| 3 | DATA (MOSI / SDA) | Pin 5 (PB0) | external → MCU | perimeter |\n| 4 | CLK (SCK / SCL) | Pin 7 (PB2) | external → MCU | perimeter |\n| 5 | CS / RST | Pin 1 (PB5 / RESET) | external → MCU | perimeter |\n| 6 | MISO / GPIO | Pin 6 (PB1) | MCU → external | perimeter |\n| 7 | GPIO / PWM | Pin 3 (PB4 / OC1B) | MCU → external | perimeter |\n| 8 | ANALOG | Pin 2 (PB3 / ADC3) | external → MCU | perimeter |\n\n## V4 Filament Drive (3 channels)\n- **Filament**: LISOCLU HUAN159 double-ended flexible filament — 3V Vf, 50mA max (25mm cut), 6500K cool white, 24mm total / 18mm active, ~2mm diameter, CRI 85. Amazon ASIN B0DGPY5WLZ.\n- **Series resistor**: YAGEO RC0603FR-0756RL (56 Ω, 1 %, 0603, 100 mW)\n- **Per-channel current**: (5 V − 3 V) / 56 Ω ≈ 35.7 mA — under ATtiny85's 40 mA/pin absolute max\n- **Resistor dissipation**: V² / R = 4 / 56 ≈ 71 mW per part (within 100 mW rating)\n- **Total LED current at full brightness**: 3 × 35.7 mA ≈ 107 mA, comfortably under the 200 mA chip-total ceiling\n- **PWM pins**: PB0 (Timer0 OC0A), PB1 (Timer0 OC0B / Timer1 OC1A), PB4 (Timer1 OC1B) — three independent hardware PWM channels\n- **PWM frequency**: ~490Hz (Timer0), ~1kHz (Timer1) — both above 200Hz flicker threshold\n\n## Pattern Storage\n- ATtiny85's on-die 512 B EEPROM holds the active pattern index and keyframe data — selected mode persists across power cycles, no extra parts required.\n\n## ProtoPart Library Status\n- Canonical ProtoPart templates applied to board templates: ATtiny85, LISOCLU Filament (updated from ADA-6141), 56 Ω Resistor.\n- 6 signal pad templates canonicalized from `gpio` → `digital` / `analog`.\n- DRC: **14 / 17 harnesses green**. The 3 ATtiny ↔ Filament harnesses are INCOMPATIBLE in the model only — canonical schema marks PWM as `digital, output` and the filament as `power, input`. Direct GPIO drive is electrically valid (well within AVR current limits); MOSFETs would only be needed to satisfy the schema, not the load.\n- **Open issue**: canonical ATtiny85 library branch (`new/attiny85`) currently models the PDIP-8 variant (ATTINY85-20PU). This board needs the SOIC-8 variant (ATTINY85-20SU). Decision: either update that branch to SOIC-8 before publish, or open a sibling branch for the SOIC variant.\n- Library branches awaiting publish go-ahead: `new/attiny85`, `new/attiny85-soic8`, `new/adafruit-ada-6141-warm-white-filament` (may need new branch for LISOCLU), `new/yageo-rc0603-56r-1pct`.\n\n## Vendor Part Numbers\n| Part | Manufacturer P/N | Vendor / SKU |\n|------|------------------|--------------|\n| Filament (cool white 6500K, cut from 300mm) | LISOCLU HUAN159 | Amazon ASIN B0DGPY5WLZ (~$1.99/2pcs) |\n| Resistor 56 Ω 0603 1% | YAGEO RC0603FR-0756RL | DigiKey 311-56.0HRCT-ND (~$0.10 q1) |\n| ATtiny85 MCU (SOIC-8) | Microchip ATTINY85-20SU | LCSC C89852 |"
    },
    "groupsById": {},
    "reviewComments": {
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "protobot",
          "authorName": "ProtoBot",
          "title": "Unlinked Harness: ATtiny85 → Warm Filament 1 (Incompatible)",
          "content": "**Issue:** Harness has no interface link configured.\\n\\n**Status:** INCOMPATIBLE - No compatible interface pairs found.\\n\\n**Analysis:**\\n- ATtiny85 has `pwm_output` interfaces (e.g., on PB4, PB0, PB1)\\n- Warm Filament 1 has a `led_drive` interface that expects power input\\n- These are different protocol types and cannot be directly linked\\n\\n**Solution Required:**\\n1. **Missing PWM LED Driver:** The LED filaments need a current-limiting resistor AND a PWM driver circuit (MOSFETs or BJTs) between MCU GPIO and LED. Currently the resistors exist, but no driver amplification.\\n2. **Alternative:** Replace LED filaments with addressable RGB LEDs (WS2812B) that accept direct MCU data signals, OR\\n3. **Add LED Driver ICs:** Use dedicated PWM LED driver (e.g., TLC5940, PCA9685) with current-limiting resistors.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** For V4 design, use the 56Ω resistor chain already present. Route PWM output through resistor to LED anode. Ground LED cathode directly. This requires updating the LED filament definition to accept PWM directly (recommend creating LED + resistor combo part).\",\n<parameter name=\"entityId\">76729891-5466-477b-a215-a97b87b6daa2\",\n<parameter name=\"entityType\">harness",
          "resolved": false,
          "id": "510895a3-8122-4597-b214-a3eace12e9eb",
          "createdAt": 1778791795148
        },
        {
